{% set schema = bolt.data.components["@bolt-components-text"].schema %}

{% macro code_example(code) %}
	<div class="t-bolt-light u-bolt-margin-bottom-small u-bolt-padding-medium">
		{% grid "o-bolt-grid--center" %}
		{% cell "u-bolt-width-12/12 u-bolt-width-6/12@medium" %}
		{{ code }}
		{% endcell %}
		{% endgrid %}
	</div>
	<div class="u-bolt-margin-bottom-large">
		<bolt-code-snippet syntax="dark" lang="html">
			{% spaceless %}
				{{ code | replace({
        '<': '&lt;',
        '>': '&gt;',
      }) | trim | raw }}
			{% endspaceless %}
		</bolt-code-snippet>
	</div>
{% endmacro %}

{% import _self as tile_code %}

{% macro video() %}
	<bolt-tile-media>
		<bolt-ratio aspect-ratio-height="9" aspect-ratio-width="16">
			<bolt-video data-setup='{"techOrder": ["Html5"], "resizeManager": false}' video-id="3861325118001" account-id="1900410236" show-meta show-meta-title player-id="r1CAdLzTW" controls></bolt-video>
		</bolt-ratio>
	</bolt-tile-media>
{% endmacro %}

{% macro image() %}
	<bolt-tile-media>
		<bolt-image src="/images/placeholders/landscape-16x9-mountains.jpg" alt="tile media."></bolt-image>
	</bolt-tile-media>
{% endmacro %}

{% macro body() %}
	<bolt-tile-body>
		<bolt-text eyebrow>This is an eyebrow</bolt-text>
		<bolt-text headline>This is a headline</bolt-text>
		<bolt-text>This is a paragraph.</bolt-text>
	</bolt-tile-body>
{% endmacro %}

{% macro body_clickable() %}
	<bolt-tile-body>This is a tile with an overall link that makes the whole tile clickable.</bolt-tile-body>
{% endmacro %}

{% macro body_with_link() %}
	<bolt-tile-body>This is a tile with an overall link that makes the whole tile clickable, while the body can still have
		<bolt-link target="_blank" url="https://boltdesignsystem.com/docs">text links</bolt-link>
		that would go somewhere else.</bolt-tile-body>
{% endmacro %}

{% macro actions() %}
	<bolt-tile-actions>
		<bolt-tile-action url="https://pega.com">
			Internal link
		</bolt-tile-action>
		<bolt-tile-action url="https://yahoo.com" external>
			External link
		</bolt-tile-action>
	</bolt-tile-actions>
{% endmacro %}

{% set tile_web_component_demo %}
<bolt-tile>
	{% include tile_code.image() %}
	{% include tile_code.body() %}
	{% include tile_code.actions() %}
</bolt-tile>
{% endset %}

{% set simple_link_demo %}
<bolt-tile url="https://google.com" url-text="Go to google.com">
	{% include tile_code.image() %}
	{% include tile_code.body_clickable() %}
</bolt-tile>
{% endset %}

{% set advanced_link_demo %}
<bolt-tile>
	<bolt-tile-link custom-attribute="foo" html-attribute="bar">
		<a href="http://google.com" target="_blank">Go to google.com</a>
	</bolt-tile-link>
	{% include tile_code.image() %}
	{% include tile_code.body_clickable() %}
</bolt-tile>
{% endset %}

{% set nested_links_demo %}
<bolt-tile url="https://google.com">
	{% include tile_code.video() %}
	{% include tile_code.body_with_link() %}
	{% include tile_code.actions() %}
</bolt-tile>
{% endset %}


<div class="o-bolt-wrapper">
	<bolt-text headline>
		Web Component Usage
	</bolt-text>
	<bolt-text>
		Bolt Text is a web component, you can simply use
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">&lt;bolt-tile&gt;</bolt-code-snippet>
		in the markup to make it render. Its inner content is comprised of
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">&lt;bolt-tile-media&gt;</bolt-code-snippet>,
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">&lt;bolt-tile-body&gt;</bolt-code-snippet>, and
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">&lt;bolt-tile-actions&gt;</bolt-code-snippet>.
	</bolt-text>
	{% include tile_code.code_example(tile_web_component_demo) %}

	<bolt-text headline>
		Simple Link Usage
	</bolt-text>
	<bolt-text>
		The simplest way to make the whole tile clickable is by passing a link address to the
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">url</bolt-code-snippet>
		prop on the main
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">&lt;bolt-tile&gt;</bolt-code-snippet>
		component itself. Also include the
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">url-text</bolt-code-snippet>
		prop for accessibility.
	</bolt-text>
	{% include tile_code.code_example(simple_link_demo) %}

	<bolt-text headline>
		Advanced Link Usage
	</bolt-text>
	<bolt-text>
		Insert a
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">&lt;bolt-tile-link&gt;</bolt-code-snippet>
		inside
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">&lt;bolt-tile&gt;</bolt-code-snippet>
		and you can pass more than just
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">url</bolt-code-snippet>.
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">&lt;bolt-tile-link&gt;</bolt-code-snippet>
		is similar to
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">&lt;bolt-link&gt;</bolt-code-snippet>. You can add custom attributes to
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">&lt;bolt-tile-link&gt;</bolt-code-snippet>
		and insert a semantic
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">&lt;a&gt;</bolt-code-snippet>
		or
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">&lt;button&gt;</bolt-code-snippet>
		element inside.
	</bolt-text>
	{% include tile_code.code_example(advanced_link_demo) %}

	<bolt-text headline>
		Nested Links
	</bolt-text>
	<bolt-text>
		While making the whole tile clickable, you are still able to insert nested links as needed. Any
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">&lt;bolt-link&gt;</bolt-code-snippet>,
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">&lt;bolt-tile-link&gt;</bolt-code-snippet>, and
		<bolt-code-snippet display="inline" lang="html">&lt;bolt-tile-action&gt;</bolt-code-snippet>
		will work as expected.
	</bolt-text>
	{% include tile_code.code_example(nested_links_demo) %}
</div>
